docs.text: set in harlem during the great depression , rival gangster " families " go to war over control of " the numbers " , an illegal gambling lottery .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: " runners " take bets from potential lottery winners and deliver them to private locations for drawings .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the undisputed leader of the harlem numbers is the madame queen ( cicely tyson ) who is challenged by dutch schulz ( tim roth ) , a ruthless hoodlum .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: by turning against the queen , dutch defies his partner , the infamous lucky luciano ( andy garcia ) , who wishes to respect the queen and keep the peace .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the queens' army strengthens when an acquaintance , ellsworth " bumpy " johnson ( lawrence fishburne ) is released from prison and becomes a bodyguard for her .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he proves himself worthy in short time as he thwarts an assassination attempt ( on himself and the queen ) , and later takes control of the queens army when she is jailed for tax evasion .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: bumpy's reign is not as restrained and subdued as the queen and he declares all out war on dutch .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: bloody gang warfare ensues .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: bumpy faces many obstacles during his reign .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: his new army questions his methods .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: his girlfriend ( vanessa l . williams ) and the queen disagree with his violent solutions .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: most importantly ( in his eyes ) , dutch has become a more formidable foe than he imagined , and seeks help from lucky luciano to assassinate him .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there have been so many movies dealing with organized crime that it must be hard to write an original story dealing with it .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this movie is not original at all .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in fact , i was angered by how many similarities there was between this film and , arguably , the best gangster movie of all time , the godfather .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if you are going to borrow ideas from another movie and not give credit , why not borrow from a lesser known movie ( say , millers crossing ? ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: how could the credited screenwriter chris brancato not give credit to mario puzo himself ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the setup in this movie is done rather well .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i enjoyed the portrayal of the network of " runners " sprinting through the streets collecting bets for the queens lottery .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this was the way of life in harlem , and most people involved with the queen did so because it was the only way to support their families and put food on the table .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: number running was the only way for the harlem population to find work .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i also enjoyed the interaction between the angry , violent dutch and the calm , patient lucky .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: after about the 30-40 minute mark all of the similarities with the godfather start appearing , one after the other ( and in short order ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it was a huge distraction , and an insult to my intelligence .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: who was the screenwriter kidding here ?

docs.text: some of the individual performances were well done .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: andy garcia was very convincing as lucky , unfortunately his screen time is reduced to a supporting role .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: tim roth effectively plays the cocky villain , much like his roles in " the cook , the thief , his wife and her lover " and " rob roy " .
docs.label: negative
